abstract: From Cairo it is learned that in a single catacomb in Upper Egypt 36 well-preserved sarcophagi of ancient royal personages have been brought to light. They represent almost all the Kings and Queens of the earlier Theban dynasty, and besides, the mummies contain parchment rolls, statues of Osiris, ornaments, and other funereal articles. Among the names of Pharaohs on these coffins are Raskenen, Amenophis I., Ahmes, Nofretari, Aahotep, Thotmes II. and III., and Rameses XII.

abstract: NANTUCKET, Mass., Aug. 5.--A dreary, sleepy place. Thus I characterized Nantucket as I sailed away from it, after my first brief visit, desiring never to return. But a capital place, I afterward reflected, in which to do some special work, or to pursue uninterruptedly a course of serious study. Circumstances have brought me again to Nantucket, and for a longer stay than my first visit.

abstract: LACHINE, Ontario, Aug. 29.--The propeller Europe, with a large schooner is tow, ran aground in Lake St. Louis last night. The pilot mistook the channel.
